// Stack Of Stacks Demo (#1560)

// No input. Has two stacks `A` and `B`. Pushes `[1, 2, 3]` onto A and `[4, 5]` onto B. Then pops all from A printing each, then pops all from B printing each. Output: `3\n2\n1\n5\n4\n`.

main

def main {
    stl.startup
    stl.output "3\n2\n1\n5\n4\n"
    stl.loop
}
